<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-06-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-06-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="318" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d318">
                        <head>No. 318.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Nelson</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-06-03"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 3,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 252.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch, No. 569, of the 16th
                            ultimo, concerning passports and certificates of matriculation in behalf
                            of American citizens, has been received. Your action, as therein
                            reported, in regard to the matter is approved.</p>
                        <p>Your dispatches numbered 570 and 571 have also been received.</p>
                        <p>I am. &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>